external_knowledge:
Golden State refers to California;
white frost is a metaphor for snow;
recent half-year means the last six months;
watchful eyes refer to monitoring stations.

sql:
SELECT report_id, report_name, data_id, report_date, file_path, file_size, generated_by, report_type, report_format, report_size_mb, report_distribution_list, report_status
FROM reports
WHERE generated_by IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT uploaded_by
    FROM data_files
);

SELECT MIN(swe_depth_inches) AS lowest_snow_depth
FROM snow_data
WHERE local_name LIKE 'L%' AND swe_depth_inches > 0;

SELECT sd.data_id, l.local_name
FROM snow_data sd
JOIN locations l ON sd.local_id = l.local_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users, COUNT(access_id) AS total_access_events
FROM access_logs
WHERE strftime('%w', access_date) BETWEEN 1 AND 5;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT local_id) 
FROM snow_data 
WHERE snow_cover_percent = 100.0;

SELECT DISTINCT s.local_id, l.local_name
FROM snow_data s
JOIN locations l ON s.local_id = l.local_id;

SELECT s.data_id, l.local_name 
FROM snow_data AS s
INNER JOIN locations AS l ON s.local_id = l.local_id;

external_knowledge:
- Snow conditions include mean snow water equivalent, depth, and precipitation; 
- User interaction data details when and how often data was accessed and by whom; 
- 'Newly issued reports' refers to any reports generated within the last seven days.
